    = image_tag('apple.jpg', class: "w-full h-full object-cover object-center", loading: :eager, style: "opacity: 0.85;")
  / Matrix-style code rain: sits above the photo (z-0) but below the dark overlay + aurora (z-10) and the z-20 text. Low opacity, brand cyan/blue, so it stays subtle and copy stays legible.
  canvas#hero-rain.absolute.inset-0.z-0 style="pointer-events:none; opacity:0.4;"
  / Overlay: lighter scrim, darker only on the left for copy legibility so the photo reads through on the right. A short bottom band resolves to solid gray-950 only at the very edge, for a crisp dark seam against the white section below.
  .absolute.inset-0.z-10 style="background-image: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(3,7,18,0.82) 0%, rgba(3,7,18,0.56) 40%, rgba(3,7,18,0.18) 72%, rgba(3,7,18,0.06) 100%), linear-gradient(to top, rgba(3,7,18,1) 0%, rgba(3,7,18,0.5) 9%, rgba(3,7,18,0) 30%);"
  / Aurora: brand-blue glow that follows the cursor + two autonomous drifting blobs. Shares z-10 with the dark overlay but paints after it (so it sits above the overlay), and stays below the z-20 text. Low alpha so copy stays legible.
